[Yoon Namno: the dispatch alarm
didn't ring during their meal.]

519
00:18:02,690 --> 00:18:04,710
No dispatches.

520
00:18:04,710 --> 00:18:05,790
No dispatches.

521
00:18:05,710 --> 00:18:08,330
[(Oh no) You can't say stuff like that.]

522
00:18:08,110 --> 00:18:10,300
Right, I should just stay quiet.

523
00:18:08,870 --> 00:18:10,410
[Watch your mouth]

524
00:18:11,060 --> 00:18:13,790
[I hope they enjoy this time fully.]

525
00:18:12,920 --> 00:18:14,050
-Please. -Don't suddenly...

526
00:18:14,010 --> 00:18:15,320
[Jung Hae-in: I hope (the alarm) doesn't ring.]

527
00:18:15,060 --> 00:18:16,840
Yes, I hope the alarm doesn't ring.

528
00:18:15,620 --> 00:18:16,860
[(Please)]

529
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:17,560
Please.

530
00:18:16,860 --> 00:18:19,120
[Ding!]

531
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:18,750
That scared me.

532
00:18:19,530 --> 00:18:22,570
What if it rings before they finish eating?

533
00:18:22,660 --> 00:18:26,480
[Kim Dohoon: 3 of their
emergency team members aren't here again.]

534
00:18:26,470 --> 00:18:27,690
You know, the 3 emergency team members,

535
00:18:27,170 --> 00:18:30,180
[The busiest in the fire station:
the emergency team]

536
00:18:27,690 --> 00:18:30,310
2 female and 1 male.

537
00:18:30,330 --> 00:18:31,830
[Kim Dohoon: They're not here.]

538
00:18:31,830 --> 00:18:33,380
[Yoon Namno: Are they dispatched?]

539
00:18:33,380 --> 00:18:34,820
[Kim Dohoon: (Just now too)
They've been constantly dispatched.]

540
00:18:35,160 --> 00:18:36,740
[Lee Kang-in: Has the emergency team eaten?]

541
00:18:36,740 --> 00:18:38,090
[Park Yoonju: They were dispatched.]

542
00:18:38,090 --> 00:18:39,980
[Lee Kang-in: So they haven't eaten.]

543
00:18:40,050 --> 00:18:42,120
-Have they had dinner? -No.

544
00:18:40,610 --> 00:18:43,750
[Worried if they had dinner on time]

545
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:43,320
Right? They haven't.

546
00:18:43,940 --> 00:18:47,900
[Jo Seondeok: When it gets extremely cold,
(dispatches) increase.]

547
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:53,190
[Jo Seondeok: It's increased a lot
(for the emergency team) this week.]

548
00:18:54,080 --> 00:18:55,830
[Lee Yoseob: It's less so for our team,]

549
00:18:55,830 --> 00:18:58,760
[Lee Yoseob: but the emergency team members
barely have time to eat.]

550
00:18:58,760 --> 00:19:00,340
[Lee Yoseob: Because they're
dispatched too frequently.]

551
00:19:00,340 --> 00:19:02,800
[Lee Yoseob: The food (turns cold) and they've
to throw it away and eat instant noodles.]

552
00:19:03,250 --> 00:19:05,620
[Lee Kang-in: The emergency team
is very busy. Indeed...]

553
00:19:05,620 --> 00:19:08,410
[Lee Kang-in: With no time to sit and rest,
they have to just head out right away...]

554
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:11,190
[Rescue dispatch! Rescue dispatch!]

555
00:19:11,700 --> 00:19:14,350
We're leaving. Thank you.

556
00:19:11,850 --> 00:19:15,000
[The alarm rings as soon as it's mentioned]

557
00:19:15,150 --> 00:19:16,990
When I think of the emergency team members,

558
00:19:15,630 --> 00:19:19,930
[The team that worries
the center director the most]

559
00:19:16,990 --> 00:19:20,710
my heart breaks for them.
Since they have it the hardest.

560
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:23,850
[Jo Seondeok: As you saw today, you barely saw
them, since they were constantly (dispatched).]

561
00:19:24,320 --> 00:19:29,610
[The busiest,
and always the last team to come back]

562
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:32,220
But for them, this workload is normal.

563
00:19:30,460 --> 00:19:34,280
[A daily schedule where
they can barely have a proper meal]

564
00:19:32,220 --> 00:19:34,370
It's like this almost every day.

565
00:19:34,410 --> 00:19:38,590
[Jo Seondeok: (The emergency team)
couldn't have lunch today either.]

566
00:19:38,680 --> 00:19:40,230
Are they still on standby?

567
00:19:39,100 --> 00:19:42,800
[Waiting for their emergency team colleagues
before having supper]

568
00:19:40,230 --> 00:19:42,770
They're still waiting. It takes a long time.

569
00:19:43,180 --> 00:19:45,980
[Moon Byungjoon: Isn't (the restaurant)
open till midnight?]

570
00:19:45,980 --> 00:19:49,070
[Moon Byungjoon: Then (the emergency team)
just have to get back by 11:30 PM.]

571
00:19:49,070 --> 00:19:51,870
[Moon Byungjoon: As long as they get back
by 11:30 PM, they can eat it.]

572
00:19:52,040 --> 00:19:55,700
[Lee Kang-in: It'd be nice if
the emergency team get to eat this too.]

573
00:19:55,050 --> 00:19:55,970
Yes.

574
00:19:56,070 --> 00:19:59,540
[Hoping they'll come and get a warm meal today]

575
00:19:59,920 --> 00:20:02,090
[They... They haven't tried
the Dubai chewy puffs?]

576
00:20:02,140 --> 00:20:02,640
No, not yet.

577
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:04,600
[(Right, my Dubai chewy puffs!)]

578
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:03,140
It's the last dish.

579
00:20:03,140 --> 00:20:04,280
It's the last one, the finale.

580
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:05,180
Because it's the dessert.

581
00:20:05,180 --> 00:20:07,120
[Go Younjung: They'd eat
the dessert last, right?]

582
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:08,830
[Full of expectations]

583
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:08,460
I'm so curious.

584
00:20:09,110 --> 00:20:12,090
[Jo Seondeok: My kids would love it
if I brought (the Dubai chewy puff) home.]

585
00:20:11,170 --> 00:20:11,790
I know.

586
00:20:12,090 --> 00:20:13,870
[Jo Seondeok: It's so hard
to buy Dubai chewy cookies.]

587
00:20:13,460 --> 00:20:15,250
-Yeah, Dubai chewy cookies. -Yeah.

588
00:20:14,500 --> 00:20:18,190
[First to try the Dubai chewy puff]

589
00:20:15,760 --> 00:20:19,830
Unless you queue up early in the morning,
you can't buy it.

590
00:20:18,610 --> 00:20:21,660
[Finishes it in two bites]

591
00:20:22,190 --> 00:20:25,030
[Is the Dubai chewy puff good?] [Yes.]

592
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:27,150
-It's delicious. -Is there cream inside?

593
00:20:27,150 --> 00:20:29,330
[The Dubai chewy puff is the best.]

594
00:20:27,900 --> 00:20:28,830
-Really? -Yeah.

595
00:20:29,710 --> 00:20:31,760
[(I'll try it too)]

596
00:20:32,550 --> 00:20:36,060
[A 119 report has been received.]

597
00:20:36,150 --> 00:20:39,410
A 119 report has been received.

598
00:20:36,530 --> 00:20:39,610
[The dispatch alarm suddenly rings]

599
00:20:39,990 --> 00:20:41,590
[But I haven't eaten my Dubai chewy puff.]

600
00:20:41,910 --> 00:20:43,020
[My puff... (sad)]

601
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:45,100
A 119 report has been received.

602
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:46,970
[In face of unexpected situations]

603
00:20:47,160 --> 00:20:49,940
I think they're leaving. Aren't they leaving?

604
00:20:47,470 --> 00:20:51,790
[Widespread panic]

605
00:20:49,990 --> 00:20:50,620
Really?

606
00:20:51,430 --> 00:20:52,800
Oh my... Gosh...

607
00:20:51,990 --> 00:20:54,460
[Hmm? Huh?]

608
00:20:59,690 --> 00:21:01,300
Fire dispatch! Fire dispatch!

609
00:20:59,890 --> 00:21:01,700
[Fire dispatch]

610
00:21:02,030 --> 00:21:03,510
[They're the fire team...]

611
00:21:03,510 --> 00:21:05,860
[Aren't they the fire team? They are!]

612
00:21:06,090 --> 00:21:07,750
[Hearing the report]

613
00:21:07,750 --> 00:21:09,640
[Running]

614
00:21:10,120 --> 00:21:14,640
[Firefighters rush out
before finishing their meal]

615
00:21:17,610 --> 00:21:20,320
[The cafeteria is empty in an instant]

616
00:21:20,780 --> 00:21:24,170
[The fire suppression team is on the move]

617
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:25,940
[The incident command team is on the move]

618
00:21:26,080 --> 00:21:27,680
[The fire investigation team is on the move]

619
00:21:33,190 --> 00:21:38,620
[Rushing to the scene immediately]

620
00:21:39,690 --> 00:21:45,360
[Flustered at the sudden turn of events]

621
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:46,660
Please.

622
00:21:49,630 --> 00:21:51,610
-They left in the middle of eating. -Yeah.

623
00:21:51,610 --> 00:21:52,960
What about the leftover food?

624
00:21:52,960 --> 00:21:55,940
[Hong Jinkyung: At least they finished.
They were nearly done eating.]

625
00:21:55,940 --> 00:21:57,610
[Kim Dohoon: Will they come back?]

626
00:21:58,690 --> 00:22:01,620
[Wait, they didn't eat the Dubai chewy puffs!]

627
00:22:00,830 --> 00:22:02,060
Oh no.

628
00:22:02,100 --> 00:22:03,420
-They left in the middle of eating. -Yeah.

629
00:22:02,590 --> 00:22:04,600
[(Sad)]

630
00:22:03,740 --> 00:22:04,850
What about the leftover food?

631
00:22:04,850 --> 00:22:07,440
[All by itself...]

632
00:22:04,950 --> 00:22:06,040
Will they come back soon?

633
00:22:06,040 --> 00:22:07,440
Will they come back soon?

634
00:22:08,080 --> 00:22:10,740
[The dispatch alarm rings again]

635
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:11,820
Was it canceled?

636
00:22:14,210 --> 00:22:15,880
[Fire dispatch! Fire dispatch!]

637
00:22:16,270 --> 00:22:19,630
[Not a cancellation but another dispatch]

638
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:19,600
We should clear those.

639
00:22:19,610 --> 00:22:20,640
There's no one here.

640
00:22:20,220 --> 00:22:23,040
[Taking the chance to clear the tables
while everyone is gone]

641
00:22:20,730 --> 00:22:21,430
Quickly.

642
00:22:25,280 --> 00:22:27,450
[They all didn't get to
eat the Dubai chewy puffs. (sad)]

643
00:22:26,840 --> 00:22:28,520
What should we do with the Dubai chewy puffs

644
00:22:27,780 --> 00:22:30,230
[No one but 1 person ate the Dubai chewy puff]

645
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:29,860
that weren't touched?

646
00:22:30,150 --> 00:22:31,280
They're good as new.

647
00:22:38,820 --> 00:22:41,240
Only the puffs weren't eaten. They're still new.

648
00:22:38,970 --> 00:22:42,020
It seems they all saved the dessert for last]

649
00:22:49,670 --> 00:22:55,600
[Clean up the tableware and cooking utensils too]

650
00:22:51,310 --> 00:22:52,080
Give it to me.

651
00:22:57,480 --> 00:23:00,340
[Dohoon is untying the bags of noodles]

652
00:23:00,950 --> 00:23:05,430
[A step that took up too much time when
they were cooking for their first customers]

653
00:23:06,010 --> 00:23:09,430
[Preparing in advance to shorten time]

654
00:23:09,870 --> 00:23:11,490
-Are you untying the bags? -Yes.

655
00:23:11,490 --> 00:23:12,840
[Nice, nice.]

656
00:23:13,140 --> 00:23:17,320
[Meticulous preparation for the next dish]

657
00:23:18,780 --> 00:23:20,240
This is cooked perfectly.

658
00:23:21,610 --> 00:23:24,520
[Drinks hot soup to replenish energy]

659
00:23:25,150 --> 00:23:27,870
[Ah! It's really delicious!]

660
00:23:29,090 --> 00:23:30,920
[Hahahaha.]

661
00:23:31,350 --> 00:23:34,920
[A dignified man who knows
to have a leisurely cup of soup]

662
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:34,260
Delicious.

663
00:23:35,740 --> 00:23:37,610
[Younjung: Are these the leftovers?]

664
00:23:36,840 --> 00:23:37,620
This one...

665
00:23:37,760 --> 00:23:38,700
[I'll eat it.]

666
00:23:38,700 --> 00:23:40,720
[Me... Me too.]

667
00:23:41,110 --> 00:23:43,850
[Unexpected time for a sugar fix]

668
00:23:41,870 --> 00:23:43,270
These are all leftovers.

669
00:23:44,260 --> 00:23:44,890
This one's big.

670
00:23:44,390 --> 00:23:49,440
[Taking care of the rest of the Dubai chewy puffs]

671
00:23:49,640 --> 00:23:51,090
-Did you eat it in one go? -Yeah.

672
00:23:54,070 --> 00:23:55,310
[A big bite]

673
00:23:57,700 --> 00:23:58,370
Is it good?

674
00:23:59,780 --> 00:24:02,880
[Especially delicious when you're tired]

675
00:24:00,220 --> 00:24:01,280
This is crazy good.

676
00:24:03,100 --> 00:24:05,130
[(Frown of approval)]

677
00:24:05,390 --> 00:24:07,070
[Jung Hae-in: It's way better
than the last batch.]

678
00:24:07,070 --> 00:24:09,170
[Yoon Namno: It's upgraded.]
[Much better.]

679
00:24:09,370 --> 00:24:10,290
And the rice cake...

680
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:13,530
[The chewy rice cake they added is the kick]

681
00:24:10,820 --> 00:24:11,870
The rice cake at the end.

682
00:24:11,870 --> 00:24:13,860
The rice cake's really the cherry on top.

683
00:24:13,860 --> 00:24:16,160
[Go Younjung: It tastes much better with
cherry jam than strawberry jam.]

684
00:24:16,140 --> 00:24:17,200
-Cherry jam? -Yes.

685
00:24:17,840 --> 00:24:18,940
The cherry jam is so good.

686
00:24:18,490 --> 00:24:21,870
[Can't stop eating]

687
00:24:19,430 --> 00:24:20,790
The sour taste gives it oomph,

688
00:24:20,790 --> 00:24:22,120
so that it isn't boring.

689
00:24:22,630 --> 00:24:24,480
[Yoon Namno: Please change your masks.]

690
00:24:23,630 --> 00:24:24,430
-Yes. -Here.

691
00:24:25,050 --> 00:24:29,920
[Tidying up while they have a break]

692
00:24:30,070 --> 00:24:31,890
[Myungsoo.]
[Yes, yes.]

693
00:24:35,370 --> 00:24:39,250
[Care (?) with a hug from behind,
sweeter than Dubai chewy puffs]

694
00:24:35,640 --> 00:24:36,460
Thank you.

695
00:24:37,030 --> 00:24:38,380
I'll clean your ears for you later.

696
00:24:38,380 --> 00:24:39,030
Why?

697
00:24:39,500 --> 00:24:40,830
You have so much earwax.

698
00:24:42,960 --> 00:24:46,360
[The order bell suddenly rings]

699
00:24:45,730 --> 00:24:46,660
Is someone here?

700
00:24:46,930 --> 00:24:47,860
2... 2 people...

701
00:24:47,980 --> 00:24:49,040
How many are there?

702
00:24:49,340 --> 00:24:49,840
2 people...

703
00:24:49,840 --> 00:24:51,510
No, wait.

704
00:24:53,110 --> 00:24:55,260
4, 5, 6, 7...

705
00:24:55,780 --> 00:24:56,510
Get 7 burners ready.

706
00:24:56,040 --> 00:24:57,340
[7 fires.]

707
00:24:57,530 --> 00:24:59,290
[Urgent]

708
00:24:57,550 --> 00:24:59,550
This is no joke. They suddenly came.

709
00:24:59,700 --> 00:25:03,660
[7 rescue team members have entered]

710
00:25:03,880 --> 00:25:05,750
[Please take a seat and wait.]

711
00:25:05,950 --> 00:25:07,230
[Hahaha.]

712
00:25:07,810 --> 00:25:10,730
[10:10 PM:
7 rescue team members have entered]

713
00:25:11,130 --> 00:25:12,810
[Yoon Namno: 7 servings of noodles in total.]

714
00:25:12,810 --> 00:25:14,640
[Yoon Namno: Divide them into 4 and 3.]

715
00:25:15,040 --> 00:25:16,460
[Heating two pans]

716
00:25:17,900 --> 00:25:21,650
[Starts to pan-fry 7 beef patties]

717
00:25:22,060 --> 00:25:24,120
[4 baskets of noodles are also being cooked]

718
00:25:22,200 --> 00:25:23,600
Turn up the heat a little.

719
00:25:24,470 --> 00:25:25,680
[7 people?]

720
00:25:26,430 --> 00:25:29,930
[Miss Hong quietly
fills the rice bowls in the corner]

721
00:25:29,950 --> 00:25:32,050
[Yoon Namno: Jinkyung, scoop seven bowls.
You're free to do it, right?]

722
00:25:32,370 --> 00:25:34,650
[7 bowls of what?]
[Of rice.]

723
00:25:34,250 --> 00:25:35,000
I've already done it.

724
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:37,010
[7 bowls of rice are ready]

725
00:25:37,060 --> 00:25:38,150
-You have? Woah. -Yes.

726
00:25:37,390 --> 00:25:38,890
[Reliable!]

727
00:25:39,320 --> 00:25:41,120
[Kim Daejoong: Good job, guys.
It's been cold today.]

728
00:25:41,170 --> 00:25:42,700
Yes, good job, everyone.

729
00:25:41,390 --> 00:25:43,520
[Exhausted...]

730
00:25:43,660 --> 00:25:45,560
[Kim Daejoong: Just a case of icicles
took the whole afternoon.]

731
00:25:45,560 --> 00:25:47,450
[Choi Jongin: (The icicles) were
more frozen than expected.]

732
00:25:47,730 --> 00:25:49,560
Watching from below,
while you were scraping it off up there,

733
00:25:47,780 --> 00:25:51,830
[Due to the sudden drop in temperature,
they've been removing icicles all day]

734
00:25:49,680 --> 00:25:51,940
it didn't look like you progressed much.

735
00:25:51,990 --> 00:25:52,580
It took so long.

736
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:54,180
[Kim Daejoong: Didn't your back hurt just now?]

737
00:25:54,070 --> 00:25:55,870
-My back hurts a lot. -Right?

738
00:25:56,180 --> 00:25:58,590
[Kim Daejoong: You've to tie (the rope)
properly so your back doesn't hurt.]

739
00:25:58,710 --> 00:26:01,600
Because you have to put in more strength,
the center of gravity shifts back.

740
00:25:58,960 --> 00:26:03,460
[Exhausted after all the intensive work]

741
00:26:03,860 --> 00:26:05,470
[It's said to be a nutritious meal.]

742
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:07,560
[Good that I didn't eat instant noodles.]
[I know, right?]

743
00:26:07,850 --> 00:26:09,900
[I planned to go crazy (?) at this meal today.]

744
00:26:10,290 --> 00:26:14,270
[Show us! Let loose today.]

745
00:26:14,580 --> 00:26:18,350
[Kim Daejoong: Better not have a dispatch now.]
[Please, no dispatches right now.]

746
00:26:18,730 --> 00:26:22,340
[Kim Daejoong: I'm going to empty my mind.
Every time we say stuff like this, it comes true.]

747
00:26:22,620 --> 00:26:24,980
[Don't they say humans are animals who grow?]

748
00:26:25,580 --> 00:26:28,060
[Left hand: cooking noodles]
[Right hand: shaking noodles]

749
00:26:28,680 --> 00:26:31,760
[He's controlling the heat with both hands]

750
00:26:32,020 --> 00:26:33,810
[Perfect teamwork]
[When will the noodles be ready?]

751
00:26:33,810 --> 00:26:35,600
[Perfect teamwork]
[In 10 seconds.]

752
00:26:34,870 --> 00:26:35,670
In 10 seconds?

753
00:26:36,300 --> 00:26:38,450
[It's better to cook it a bit more.]

754
00:26:38,890 --> 00:26:40,110
[Wait a minute.]

755
00:26:40,600 --> 00:26:43,440
[Gradually grasps the feeling of
when the noodles are cooked well]

756
00:26:41,740 --> 00:26:42,410
Done, done.

757
00:26:43,840 --> 00:26:45,110
[Slips in]

758
00:26:45,420 --> 00:26:47,120
[Hae-in, you're cooking them so well.]

759
00:26:47,590 --> 00:26:49,660
[Golden brown]

760
00:26:48,510 --> 00:26:49,310
So beautiful.

761
00:26:49,820 --> 00:26:50,320
Thank you.

762
00:26:50,240 --> 00:26:53,080
[As everyone is basking in the joy of growth]

763
00:26:50,380 --> 00:26:51,570
Looks like a full moon.

764
00:26:51,570 --> 00:26:52,250
Thank you.

765
00:26:53,480 --> 00:26:55,760
[Put the chicken with me.]

766
00:26:54,420 --> 00:26:54,940
What?

767
00:26:55,020 --> 00:26:56,370
Put the chicken when the noodles

768
00:26:56,370 --> 00:26:57,000
are out.

769
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:59,810
[You never taught me this!]
[Namno: If you have 2 hands, you can do it.]

770
00:27:00,100 --> 00:27:01,330
Put them like this.

771
00:27:00,410 --> 00:27:02,880
[Mr. Park, who dislikes rapid growth]

772
00:27:03,240 --> 00:27:04,980
[You haven't taught me this...]
[A bit more.]

773
00:27:05,050 --> 00:27:07,180
[Yes, Chef!]

774
00:27:06,050 --> 00:27:06,810
OK, good.

775
00:27:07,600 --> 00:27:09,340
Are the 4 bowls ready? Move them here.

776
00:27:07,650 --> 00:27:09,240
[Takes the noodle soup]

777
00:27:10,020 --> 00:27:13,520
[Garnishes tossed to him
as soon as he puts down the bowl]

778
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:11,500
Red chilis.

779
00:27:12,580 --> 00:27:13,750
Give me the red chilis.

780
00:27:13,750 --> 00:27:14,950
-You want me to do it? -Yes.

781
00:27:14,020 --> 00:27:16,570
[Whining while doing everything as instructed]

782
00:27:15,040 --> 00:27:15,950
You never taught me this!

783
00:27:15,950 --> 00:27:16,610
This one...

784
00:27:16,990 --> 00:27:22,500
[It's me, Mr. 10 Jobs]

785
00:27:17,040 --> 00:27:17,710
Like this?

786
00:27:17,780 --> 00:27:19,110
OK. Done.

787
00:27:20,230 --> 00:27:22,690
OK, now let's get to it for real. Do a neat job.

788
00:27:23,230 --> 00:27:24,270
You need to get the rice ready, Ma'am.

789
00:27:23,240 --> 00:27:25,920
[While whining non-stop]

790
00:27:24,520 --> 00:27:25,090
You do it.

791
00:27:25,200 --> 00:27:25,980
Now I'm doing it.

792
00:27:25,980 --> 00:27:27,470
Whoever is free can do it.

793
00:27:26,270 --> 00:27:29,750
[His hands are working obediently]

794
00:27:27,530 --> 00:27:29,750
It's so busy
I can't cope even if I have 10 of me!

795
00:27:29,750 --> 00:27:31,080
[Set the cutlery]

796
00:27:31,080 --> 00:27:32,900
[Plate the kimchi]

797
00:27:32,900 --> 00:27:34,290
[Set the rice]

798
00:27:34,290 --> 00:27:35,800
[Move the knife-cut noodles]

799
00:27:34,560 --> 00:27:35,490
Give it to me now.

800
00:27:35,800 --> 00:27:37,800
[Move the beef patties]

801
00:27:36,120 --> 00:27:37,120
The beef patties.

802
00:27:37,800 --> 00:27:40,840
[Add the noodle garnishes]

803
00:27:39,740 --> 00:27:40,590
Red chilis.

804
00:27:40,840 --> 00:27:42,790
[Untie the bags of noodles]

805
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:43,310
A total of 7 servings of noodles.

806
00:27:42,790 --> 00:27:44,690
[Plate the beef patties]

807
00:27:44,690 --> 00:27:47,000
[Clean up the surroundings]

808
00:27:45,010 --> 00:27:46,380
Put these away?

809
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:49,170
[Do the dishes]

810
00:27:49,170 --> 00:27:50,180
Move. I need to work.

811
00:27:50,180 --> 00:27:51,130
I need to work. Move.

812
00:27:51,130 --> 00:27:52,920
[Add the noodle garnishes] [Again and again]

813
00:27:53,570 --> 00:27:57,340
[Infinite Chore Hell]

814
00:27:57,770 --> 00:27:59,240
[Myungsoo, you're doing a great job!]

815
00:27:59,520 --> 00:28:02,120
[Mr. 10 Jobs survives]

816
00:27:59,880 --> 00:28:01,620
It's not like I did everything.

817
00:28:02,310 --> 00:28:03,300
4 beef patties are ready.

818
00:28:03,300 --> 00:28:04,560
OK. Thank you.

819
00:28:03,520 --> 00:28:05,080
[(Passes on the beef patties)]

820
00:28:05,350 --> 00:28:08,270
Put it here, and here.

821
00:28:05,460 --> 00:28:08,400
[Finishes 4 beef patties in that time too]

822
00:28:08,680 --> 00:28:09,580
-Is it done? -Yes.

823
00:28:08,950 --> 00:28:13,180
[Continues cooking the remaining 3 beef patties]

824
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:15,160
[Huh? Wait a minute.]

825
00:28:15,340 --> 00:28:17,960
[Namno checks the beef patties closely]

826
00:28:16,100 --> 00:28:16,820
This is...

827
00:28:18,420 --> 00:28:21,330
[Overcooked beef patties]

828
00:28:18,820 --> 00:28:20,020
Are they overcooked?

829
00:28:20,370 --> 00:28:23,490
Yeah. Remove these and make 3 new ones.

830
00:28:25,760 --> 00:28:28,630
[Has to make the 3 beef patties again]

831
00:28:29,010 --> 00:28:29,550
It's OK.

832
00:28:30,690 --> 00:28:32,890
[Yoon Namno: They get burnt easily
because of the soy sauce.]

833
00:28:33,620 --> 00:28:36,150
[Jung Hae-in: I should use low heat, right?]

834
00:28:34,790 --> 00:28:35,710
Use low heat.

835
00:28:36,370 --> 00:28:37,040
Are they burnt?

836
00:28:36,550 --> 00:28:40,300
[Hae-in face turns stiff
after making another mistake]

837
00:28:37,360 --> 00:28:39,200
A little. But I like it like this.

838
00:28:40,850 --> 00:28:43,350
[Yoon Namno: We'll eat these burnt ones.]

839
00:28:42,760 --> 00:28:43,370
OK.

840
00:28:43,610 --> 00:28:46,590
Put this here, and here.

841
00:28:43,760 --> 00:28:47,040
[4 sets have been finished]

842
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:50,070
[Sends out the 4 sets first]

843
00:28:47,920 --> 00:28:51,320
4 servings are out.
Please come forward to collect your food.

844
00:28:52,530 --> 00:28:56,920
[A nutritious meal for the exhausted men!]

845
00:28:57,200 --> 00:28:57,890
[Wow.]

846
00:28:58,960 --> 00:29:00,210
-This isn't supper...
-Wow, there are Dubai chewy cookies.

847
00:29:00,210 --> 00:29:01,690
-What? Dubai chewy cookies? -Dubai chewy cookies!

848
00:29:01,690 --> 00:29:03,200
-Dubai chewy cookies. -Dubai chewy cookies.

849
00:29:03,150 --> 00:29:05,040
[Can we eat this?]

850
00:29:04,170 --> 00:29:05,380
Is this really the Dubai chewy cookie?

851
00:29:05,380 --> 00:29:08,560
[I'm glad I came to Bucheon Fire Station.]

852
00:29:08,890 --> 00:29:12,120
[Luckily we're on duty today!]

853
00:29:10,060 --> 00:29:10,920
I know.

854
00:29:12,470 --> 00:29:16,240
[Can't forget to take photos]

855
00:29:16,620 --> 00:29:19,450
[While it's still hot, they try the supper]

856
00:29:16,780 --> 00:29:18,780
I usually don't take photos of food.

857
00:29:19,540 --> 00:29:22,300
A 119 report has been received.

858
00:29:20,250 --> 00:29:20,890
[Ah...] [Ah...] [Ah...]

859
00:29:22,490 --> 00:29:25,680
A 119 report has been received.

860
00:29:22,970 --> 00:29:28,050
[Speak of the devil! The dispatch alarm rings]

861
00:29:28,460 --> 00:29:29,730
[Kim Daejoong: It's my fault. I jinxed it.]

862
00:29:29,730 --> 00:29:31,720
[Choi Jongin: Let's hear (the details)
of the dispatch vehicle first.]

863
00:29:32,940 --> 00:29:37,490
[Are they going be dispatched again?]

864
00:29:33,880 --> 00:29:35,910
Fire! Fire!

865
00:29:37,870 --> 00:29:42,380
[The dispatch teams are decided
based on the report details]

866
00:29:43,760 --> 00:29:45,290
[Fire dispatch!]

867
00:29:45,600 --> 00:29:48,430
[Dispatch vehicle:
Central Pump, Central Chemical...]

868
00:29:48,430 --> 00:29:51,670
[Not a dispatch for the rescue team!]

869
00:29:52,040 --> 00:29:56,070
[Don't forget that the word "dispatch" is taboo]

870
00:29:52,360 --> 00:29:54,160
I'm sorry. I won't talk anymore.

871
00:29:54,270 --> 00:29:55,670
That's a forbidden word.

872
00:29:56,060 --> 00:29:58,810
But they're not from the fire team, are they?

873
00:29:56,620 --> 00:29:59,710
[Getting nervous as well]

874
00:29:59,870 --> 00:30:02,170
[Looks like it's another team...]

875
00:30:02,440 --> 00:30:05,520
[Yoon Namno: Constantly on pins and needles,
how can they enjoy their meal?]

876
00:30:06,260 --> 00:30:07,040
OK.

877
00:30:06,340 --> 00:30:09,330
[Checks the beef patties again]

878
00:30:09,330 --> 00:30:10,650
[Hae-in: I think these are good.]

879
00:30:11,850 --> 00:30:13,020
[Chef.]

880
00:30:13,230 --> 00:30:14,950
[Jung Hae-in: Can you check them?]

881
00:30:15,220 --> 00:30:17,270
[A bit longer!]

882
00:30:16,060 --> 00:30:17,260
-A bit longer? -Yes.

883
00:30:17,260 --> 00:30:20,390
Pan-fry them covered for 30 seconds each,
on both sides.

884
00:30:20,680 --> 00:30:23,320
[Checks the time with the timer]

885
00:30:23,670 --> 00:30:25,640
[Anxious...]

886
00:30:25,990 --> 00:30:29,430
[Hae-in stares at the beef patties without moving]

887
00:30:30,960 --> 00:30:32,450
[Peeking]

888
00:30:33,030 --> 00:30:35,970
[The trays are just missing the beef patties]

889
00:30:36,400 --> 00:30:38,880
[Super stressed]

890
00:30:39,620 --> 00:30:42,740
[Fidgeting from anxiety]

891
00:30:45,860 --> 00:30:47,920
[Thoroughly checking the beef patties,
even the edges]

892
00:30:50,100 --> 00:30:51,790
[It's hot. Not yet.]
[Grabs it]

893
00:30:51,800 --> 00:30:52,620
It's hot.

894
00:30:52,560 --> 00:30:54,290
[It's OK! My hands are cold (?), so it's OK.]

895
00:30:54,710 --> 00:30:57,310
[Thanks to Younjung's help with plating]

896
00:30:57,590 --> 00:31:00,820
[Phew, 3 well-cooked beef patties are out]

897
00:31:03,200 --> 00:31:05,060
-The beef patties are ready. -Yes.

898
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:06,670
[The remaining 3 servings are done]

899
00:31:06,710 --> 00:31:08,330
3 servings are out.
Please come forward to collect your food.

900
00:31:08,330 --> 00:31:09,590
Thank you for the food.

901
00:31:09,730 --> 00:31:10,770
-Let's eat. -Let's eat.

902
00:31:10,770 --> 00:31:12,680
-Let's eat. -Enjoy.

903
00:31:13,530 --> 00:31:17,210
[Will the 2nd batch, the rescue team members,
have a great supper as well?]

904
00:31:17,590 --> 00:31:19,920
[Trying the soup first]
[Ah!]

905
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:21,730
[Trying the soup first]

906
00:31:20,600 --> 00:31:22,200
Seafood Knife-Cut Noodles.

907
00:31:24,170 --> 00:31:25,040
It's delicious.

908
00:31:25,040 --> 00:31:25,860
Abalone!

909
00:31:26,110 --> 00:31:27,530
[Lee Hyung Won: There's abalone inside!]

910
00:31:27,680 --> 00:31:29,330
-There's abalone? -Yes, abalone.

911
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:30,630
[A whole abalone inside!]

912
00:31:29,330 --> 00:31:30,800
-Ah, this is it. -Yeah.

913
00:31:30,930 --> 00:31:32,540
[So delicious!]

914
00:31:33,020 --> 00:31:35,780
[Kim Daejoong: This is beyond a supper snack.]

915
00:31:36,030 --> 00:31:38,660
[Choi Jongin: I feel like
I'm having a proper meal.]

916
00:31:38,970 --> 00:31:40,990
[Kim Daejoong: Is there a famous chef in there?]

917
00:31:41,120 --> 00:31:42,710
[Kim Daejoong: Don't you think]

918
00:31:42,850 --> 00:31:45,320
[Kim Daejoong: such a great meal
must've been cooked by a famous chef?]

919
00:31:45,670 --> 00:31:47,290
[More customers are here!]

920
00:31:46,770 --> 00:31:47,680
Where?

921
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:48,660
Oh, oh, oh.

922
00:31:47,900 --> 00:31:50,300
[Customers keep coming in]

923
00:31:49,350 --> 00:31:50,260
Get ready!

924
00:31:50,570 --> 00:31:52,480
[They're here!]

925
00:31:51,330 --> 00:31:52,400
Oh no. This will be chaos.

926
00:31:52,400 --> 00:31:53,770
Hey, this will be chaos.

927
00:31:53,970 --> 00:31:56,110
2... and 3 people are here.

928
00:31:54,110 --> 00:31:56,340
[2 from the fire investigation team]
[3 from Central Control Center]

929
00:31:56,340 --> 00:31:58,720
[(Quickly)] [(Quickly)]

930
00:31:56,840 --> 00:31:57,950
Put the noodles in.

931
00:31:59,280 --> 00:32:01,200
[(Jinkyung helps)]

932
00:32:01,550 --> 00:32:02,460
Put them in?

933
00:32:01,630 --> 00:32:05,060
[Kim Dohoon: You need to
shake it a little before adding them in.]

934
00:32:04,800 --> 00:32:06,060
-Shake it? -Yes.

935
00:32:05,560 --> 00:32:08,700
[No matter how busy it gets,
you have to loosen the noodles well]

936
00:32:09,020 --> 00:32:10,110
Thank you.

937
00:32:11,100 --> 00:32:12,950
[Yoon Namno: When we (plate it,)]

938
00:32:13,090 --> 00:32:15,810
[Yoon Namno: try not to get oil
on the rim of the plate.]

939
00:32:16,150 --> 00:32:19,430
[Gets some paper towels immediately]

940
00:32:21,040 --> 00:32:21,770
OK.

941
00:32:21,450 --> 00:32:24,650
[Wipes the oil]

942
00:32:21,770 --> 00:32:23,110
Hurry. Hurry.

943
00:32:24,880 --> 00:32:26,880
Food for 2 is ready.

944
00:32:25,100 --> 00:32:28,540
[Meals prepared with
their cooperative contributions]

945
00:32:29,530 --> 00:32:31,440
Open it. Without revealing us.

946
00:32:31,680 --> 00:32:33,930
[Supper for 2 is delivered]

947
00:32:34,960 --> 00:32:36,220
[Thank you for the food.]

948
00:32:36,360 --> 00:32:37,850
[Please enjoy!]

949
00:32:38,300 --> 00:32:40,560
[Did you get a spoon?]

950
00:32:39,980 --> 00:32:41,070
They didn't give...

951
00:32:41,070 --> 00:32:42,270
[You didn't get a spoon.]

952
00:32:44,450 --> 00:32:45,800
[Knock, knock]

953
00:32:49,010 --> 00:32:51,500
Bae Giseok: I think
you didn't give us spoons, haha.]

954
00:32:51,870 --> 00:32:53,900
[When they sent the food out]

955
00:32:56,450 --> 00:32:58,260
[Urgent]

956
00:32:58,580 --> 00:32:59,920
[What's wrong?]

957
00:32:59,880 --> 00:33:00,710
I'm sorry.

958
00:33:00,710 --> 00:33:01,840
Why? What happened?

959
00:33:02,750 --> 00:33:04,000
Thank you.

960
00:33:05,170 --> 00:33:06,130
[You didn't give them spoons?]

961
00:33:07,190 --> 00:33:10,610
[So flustered that she can only laugh]

962
00:33:08,800 --> 00:33:10,040
Why are you laughing?

963
00:33:10,960 --> 00:33:13,820
[I... I didn't give them spoons.]

964
00:33:12,510 --> 00:33:13,770
Why not?

965
00:33:14,080 --> 00:33:16,730
[Park Myungsoo: What are you talking about?
They were all placed here.]

966
00:33:15,530 --> 00:33:16,840
Except spoons.

967
00:33:17,050 --> 00:33:19,660
[The spoons were missing]

968
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:21,420
-Only chopsticks. -Really?

969
00:33:20,330 --> 00:33:22,310
[Embarrassed]

970
00:33:22,540 --> 00:33:24,510
[Go Younjung: I missed it. Sorry.]

971
00:33:24,770 --> 00:33:26,550
-Eat up. -Thank you.

972
00:33:27,790 --> 00:33:31,860
[Drinks the hot soup with his new spoon]

973
00:33:32,210 --> 00:33:34,320
[The rescue team members are
engrossed in their meals]

974
00:33:34,600 --> 00:33:38,970
[Focused solely on the food, eating aggressively]

975
00:33:39,510 --> 00:33:41,860
[Picks up the bowl to gulp the soup!]

976
00:33:43,600 --> 00:33:45,260
[Sweating profusely]

977
00:33:45,260 --> 00:33:46,750
It's a huge meal.

978
00:33:45,720 --> 00:33:48,050
[Looks like he did go crazy at his meal]

979
00:33:49,750 --> 00:33:51,940
[Kim Daejoong: You guys are
so funny right now, you know?]

980
00:33:52,050 --> 00:33:53,650
[Kim Daejoong: Eating the delicious meal
so urgently.]

981
00:33:54,230 --> 00:33:56,560
[Afraid we won't get to eat
(if we get dispatched)]

982
00:33:56,890 --> 00:33:59,900
[Eat slowly. They said they'd
replace the meals for us again.]

983
00:33:58,480 --> 00:33:59,240
OK.

984
00:34:00,570 --> 00:34:02,310
[Gosh, it's exhausting...]

985
00:34:02,260 --> 00:34:04,550
You must be tired.

986
00:34:02,940 --> 00:34:04,630
[Park Myungsoo: No time to even drink water.]

987
00:34:05,140 --> 00:34:06,730
[Slips in]

988
00:34:05,570 --> 00:34:07,300
-Here you go, big brother. -OK.

989
00:34:07,340 --> 00:34:11,360
[A hydration fairy appears
at the perfect time]

990
00:34:12,710 --> 00:34:14,860
[I can breathe again…]

991
00:34:15,480 --> 00:34:18,000
[Also brings essential hydration to Hae-in,
who's been working hard before the fire]

992
00:34:16,679 --> 00:34:17,639
Thank you.

993
00:34:21,370 --> 00:34:22,929
[Ah!]

994
00:34:23,969 --> 00:34:24,830
So refreshing.

995
00:34:25,199 --> 00:34:26,199
-Jinkyung. -Yeah?

996
00:34:25,500 --> 00:34:31,610
[The hydration fairy takes care of his crew first]

997
00:34:26,440 --> 00:34:28,310
-Thank you. -I'll leave it here.

998
00:34:28,310 --> 00:34:29,330
Have some water.

999
00:34:29,340 --> 00:34:30,570
-I'll leave it behind here. -Thank you.

1000
00:34:30,570 --> 00:34:31,969
-Behind the lids. -OK.

1001
00:34:32,820 --> 00:34:35,920
[Brings water to everyone]

1002
00:34:36,340 --> 00:34:38,010
[Before he has a sip...]

1003
00:34:38,010 --> 00:34:39,690
[A sip?]

1004
00:34:39,949 --> 00:34:42,460
[Downs the bottle in one gulp]

1005
00:34:42,710 --> 00:34:45,040
[It's understandable (?) why
he downs the entire bottle]

1006
00:34:42,750 --> 00:34:43,969
We need to cook 4 more servings of noodles, right?

1007
00:34:43,969 --> 00:34:45,000
Just 3 more.

1008
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:46,040
-3? -Yes.

1009
00:34:46,040 --> 00:34:48,219
-You're cooking 5 now? -Yes, 5.

1010
00:34:46,100 --> 00:34:49,010
[Prepares the noodles in advance]

1011
00:34:49,530 --> 00:34:51,730
-Where did it go? -I'll bring you the blowtorch.

1012
00:34:51,730 --> 00:34:52,750
I'll do it for you.

1013
00:34:52,030 --> 00:34:54,840
[Instantly picking up on
what's troubling his crew]

1014
00:34:54,820 --> 00:34:56,400
Wait, let me set the plates for you.

1015
00:34:55,239 --> 00:34:59,560
[Chef Namno filled in the gaps in the kitchen]

1016
00:34:56,600 --> 00:34:57,570
Thank you.

1017
00:35:00,200 --> 00:35:03,270
[His first bite of the Dubai chewy puff]

1018
00:35:03,990 --> 00:35:05,890
[Is anyone eating the Dubai chewy puffs?]

1019
00:35:04,970 --> 00:35:05,930
He's eating it.

1020
00:35:05,930 --> 00:35:06,680
That guy.

1021
00:35:06,290 --> 00:35:08,250
[Nervous]

1022
00:35:08,700 --> 00:35:11,490
[How are the Dubai chewy puffs made by Younjung?]

1023
00:35:11,950 --> 00:35:13,820
[Mm!]

1024
00:35:13,820 --> 00:35:14,800
Wow, Yeongsu.

1025
00:35:15,230 --> 00:35:16,830
[Mm! (Try it)]

1026
00:35:16,830 --> 00:35:17,940
